  "description": "Variation of condition 1 of listed building consent dated 3 April 2018 (RN: 17/10530/LBC) for 'Alterations to the existing building including removal of existing roof top plant and extension to create an additional storey at fifth floor with tiled mansards and lead clad dormer windows to front and rear; a single storey extension at fourth floor comprising a glazed dome above the existing rear bow; installation of plant at roof level; partial infilling of lightwell adjacent to Gwydyr House; facade cleaning and other facade repair; internal alterations including reconfiguration, fabric removal, and refurbishment works on all floors; refurbishment of meetings rooms, entrance reception and offices; installation of new heating and cooling equipment; provision of a glazed research pod in the library; installation of light-boxes above the central stair and library, and other associated works'.  Namely, to vary the approved drawing numbers to make amendments including a reduction in size of the glazed dome and automatic opening vent, increase in size of the plant area, omission of a rooflight bay and internal alterations.",
